timeline.bodyText:
and cannot access the {siem-app}

It is possible run a local (non-Elastic Cloud) instance without security enabled and still access the SIEM app, however the user will see the Detection engine permissions required message on the Overview page (in place of the Signals histogram), and the same message will appear in the Detections page.
Consider changing:
and cannot access the {siem-app}

to something like:
and you see the 'Detection engine permissions' required message in the Overview or Detections page
